race.comment: LORD VETTORI (3) consistent gelding who resumed with a slick Maiden win over 1115m at Grafton. Up in trip and grade when an eye-catching second over 1200m at Beaumont (Newcastle). Only has to hold that form to be winning this. MIRAI SAN (4) was a new acquisition for the Scott Singleton stable when he shouldered the 60.5kg for a slashing third over 1200m at Scone. Clearly returned in good order and shapes as the main danger. HERMAN SAID (6) lightly raced gelding expected to race a little closer to the speed third-up. Drifted back from the awkward gate when fifth over 1200m at Beaumont (Newcastle). Ready to take a hand in the finish. ETOILE FILANTE (1) hard fit for this and was strong through the line when third over 1200m at Beaumont (Newcastle). No excuses today from the good gate.
